HEADWORD: Convulsionist
<hw>Con*vul"sion*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who has convulsions;
esp., one of a body of fanatics in France, early in the eighteenth
century, who went into convulsions under the influence of religious
emotion; <as>as, the <ex>Convulsionists</ex> of St.
M⟦eacute⟧dard</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Convulsive</ent>⟦br⟧
